412 template <typename T>
413 class WeakCallbackInfo {
414  public:
415  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
416 
417  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
418  void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
419  Callback* callback)
420  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
421  for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
422  internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
423  }
424  }
425 
426  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
427  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
428  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
429 
430  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
431  void* GetInternalField1() const) {
432  return internal_fields_[0];
433  }
434  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
435  void* GetInternalField2() const) {
436  return internal_fields_[1];
437  }
438 
439  V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
440  bool IsFirstPass() const) {
441  return callback_ != nullptr;
442  }
443 
444  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
445  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
446  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
447  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
448  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
449  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
450  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
451 
452  private:
453  Isolate* isolate_;
454  T* parameter_;
455  Callback* callback_;
456  void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
457 };

483 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
484 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
485 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
486 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
487 // possible to request a second pass callback.
488 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

578  // Phantom persistents work like weak persistents, except that the pointer to
579  // the object being collected is not available in the finalization callback.
580  // This enables the garbage collector to collect the object and any objects
581  // it references transitively in one GC cycle. At the moment you can either
582  // specify a parameter for the callback or the location of two internal
583  // fields in the dying object.
584  template <typename P>

586  "use SetWeak",
587  void SetPhantom(P* parameter,
588  typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
589  int internal_field_index1 = -1,
590  int internal_field_index2 = -1));

6730 template <class T>
6731 class Maybe {
6732  public:
6733  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value; }
6734  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value; }
6735 
6736  // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
6737  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
6738  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
6739  return value;
6740  }
6741 
6742  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
6743  return has_value ? value : default_value;
6744  }
6745 
6746  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
6747  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
6748  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
6749  }
6750 
6751  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
6752  return !operator==(other);
6753  }
6754 
6755  private:
6756  Maybe() : has_value(false) {}
6757  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value(true), value(t) {}
6758 
6759  bool has_value;
6760  T value;
6761 
6762  template <class U>
6763  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
6764  template <class U>
6765  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
6766 };
6767

6769 template <class T>
6770 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
6771  return Maybe<T>();
6772 }
6773 
6774 
6775 template <class T>
6776 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
6777  return Maybe<T>(t);

7272 // Tag information for HeapObject.
7273 const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
7274 const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
7275 const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
7276 
7277 // Tag information for Smi.
7278 const int kSmiTag = 0;
7279 const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
7280 const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
7281 
7282 template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
7283 
7284 template<int kSmiShiftSize>
7285 V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7286  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7287  uintptr_t tagged_value =
7288  (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
7289  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
7290 }
7291 
7292 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
7293 template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
7294  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
7295  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7296  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7297  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7298  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7299  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
7300  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
7301  }
7302  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7303  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7304  }
7305  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7306  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
7307  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
7308  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
7309  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
7310  //
7311  // CAUTION: The original code below:
7312  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
7313  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
7314  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
7315  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
7316  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
7317  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
7318  }
7319 };
7320 
7321 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
7322 template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
7323  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
7324  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7325  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7326  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7327  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7328  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
7329  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
7330  }
7331  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7332  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7333  }
7334  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7335  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
7336  return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
7337  }
7338 };

7459  bool value, int shift) {

7513  I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);

8032 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
8033 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8034  typedef internal::Object O;
8035  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
8036  typedef internal::Internals I;
8037  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
8038  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
8039  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
8040  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
8041  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
8042  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType) {
8043  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8044  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
8045  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
8046  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
8047  }
8048 #endif
8049  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
8050 }
8051 
8052 
8053 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
8054 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8055  typedef internal::Object O;
8056  typedef internal::Internals I;
8057  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
8058  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
8059  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
8060  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
8061  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
8062  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType)) {
8063  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8064  return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
8065  }
8066 #endif
8067  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
8068 }

8106 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
8107  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
8108  typedef internal::Object O;
8109  typedef internal::Internals I;
8110  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
8111  int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
8112  *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
8113  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;

8115  type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
8116  void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
8117  resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);

8121 #endif

8610 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
8611  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
8612  typedef internal::Internals I;
8613  int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory =
8614  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
8615  I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryOffset);
8616  int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc =
8617  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
8618  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
8619  I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryAtLastGlobalGCOffset);
8620  int64_t amount = *amount_of_external_allocated_memory + change_in_bytes;
8621  if (change_in_bytes > 0 &&
8622  amount - *amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc >
8623  I::kExternalAllocationLimit) {
8624  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
8625  }
8626  *amount_of_external_allocated_memory = amount;
8627  return *amount_of_external_allocated_memory;
8628 }
